Tammy Petersen, News24(File, Ted S Warren, AP) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Bhisho - An 81-year-old woman who pleaded guilty to possession of dagga plants was warned and released after appearing in the Willowvale Magistrate's Court on Friday, Eastern Cape police said.Nowezile Mncoko was arrested on Wednesday after officers spotted the dagga plants growing in her garden in Mente village, Captain Jackson Manatha said.Officers uprooted them and charged her with possession. The eight confiscated plants had an estimated street value of R2500.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.